      • forEach

        public <H extends RowHandler<? super T>> H forEach(ResultSet rs,
                                                   H handler)
                                            throws SQLException,
                                                   MappingException
        Description copied from interface: JdbcMapper
        Loop over the resultSet, map each row to a new instance of T and call back the handler

        The method will return the handler passed as an argument so you can easily chain the calls like
        List<T> list = jdbcMapper.forEach(rs, new ListHandler<T>()).getList();

        Specified by:
        forEach in interface JdbcMapper<T>
        Type Parameters:

        Returns:
        the handler passed in
        Throws:

        MappingException - if an error occurs during the mapping
